
source <(talosctl completion zsh)
1. Bootstrap the first control-plane

Generating Talos Configuration using Talhelper

Generate Talos secrets.
  talhelper gensecret
  talhelper gensecret > talsecret.sops.yaml
talhelper gensecret > talsecret.sops.cla.yaml
talhelper gensecret > talsecret.sops.clb.yaml
talhelper gensecret > talsecret.sops.clc.yaml

Create Age secret key.
  mkdir -p $HOME/.config/sops/age/
  age-keygen -o $HOME/.config/sops/age/keys.txt

creation_rules:
  - age: >-
   <age-public-key> ## get this in the keys.txt file from previous step

Encrypt Talos secrets with Age and Sops.
  sops -e -i talsecret.sops.yaml
sops -e -i talsecret.sops.cla.yaml
sops -e -i talsecret.sops.clb.yaml
sops -e -i talsecret.sops.clc.yaml

Generate Talos configuration
  talhelper genconfig -o clusterconfig/a -c talconfig-a.yaml -s talsecret.sops.cla.yaml -n
  talhelper genconfig -o clusterconfig/b -c talconfig-b.yaml -s talsecret.sops.clb.yaml -n 
  talhelper genconfig -o clusterconfig/c -c talconfig-c.yaml -s talsecret.sops.clc.yaml -n 

Configuration for each Talos node will be generated in clusterconfig directory.

talosctl -n 192.168.1.110 get disks --insecure
talosctl -n 192.168.1.110 get cpu --insecure
talosctl -n 192.168.1.113 get rd --insecure
